Always seem to be out of stock regarding different items as well as syrups for their lattes. Staff seems, for the most part, as if they'd rather not be there. In fact, they remind me of the Greek diner scene on SNL many, many years ago. The only way that you can get a positive reaction from any of them is if you just accept the inevitable that you have to take whatever they give you or leave. Even though I am finding the Starbucks experience to be nothing better than distasteful and have stopped frequenting this store, as well as many other locations. The truth is that coffee is coffee, and I am sure that, even at their bloated prices, they are not hurting. Though it would be nice if they would try to improve.
